#which endpoints are public

GET

#which field are required on create

POST -> strict
PATCH -> flexible 
PUT -> full replacement 

#what clients are allowed to edit.

The client are allowed to edit text question responses by a student role.

#what must the client send?
A client must return a get request when it is requested.

#what may the client send?

A client may return json api request for development use.

#what will the server always return

The server wil return GET requests.
The server will return list of responses per questions for the role of educator
The server will return list of assigned questions for the role of student

#what errors are guaranteed?

clients are rely on:

-status code
-error shapes
-validation messages

#what is forbidden?
It is forbiddened, to a user with role of student to delete a question that is assigned. 
It is forbidenned to a user with role of student to submit two different responses for a specific questions.
It is forbidenned to a user with role of educator to change or edit submitted responses.

#who is allowed to use?

Public(no auth)
But still restricted by behaviour

#Example:

Educator submits → POST /response/

Admin edits question → PATCH /question/:id/

TextQuestionContainer

### POST /http://127.0.0.1:8000/api/container

purpose: Admin creates a text question container

# Optional Values
-description 

-is_active

# Mandatory values
-title

# Editable fields
-title

-description 

-is_active

### PATCH /http://127.0.0.1:8000/api/container

purpose: Admin edits a field of a text question container

# Editable fields

-title 

-description

# Non Editable fields

-is_active

-----------------------------------------

TextQuestion 
------------

### POST /http://127.0.0.1:8000/api/question

purpose: Admin creates text question

# Optional values

-is_active

# Mandatory values

-title 

-text_question_container

-question_number_id

# Editable fields

-title
-is_active

# Immutable fields

-question_number_id
-text_question_container


### PATCH /http://127.0.0.1:8000/api/question/2/

purpose:  An educator can edit a single text question 

# Optional values 

-title
-is_active

# Not editable

-question_number_id
-text_question_container

------------------------------------------
TextResponse 
------------

### POST / http://127.0.0.1:8000/api/question/1/responses/

purpose: A response is submitted by a user that has a role of student

# Optional values

- response_number_id

# Mandatory Values

- response_text
- text_question

# Mutable Values

- response_text
- text_question

# Non Imutable values

- response_number_id


### PATCH /http://127.0.0.1:8000/api/question/1/responses

purpose: A specific response can be edit by a student, before final submitting

# Optional values

- text_question
- response_number_id

# Editable values

- response_text


# Non editable values

- text_question
- response_number_id
